                <h2>ESP32 Introduction</h2>
                <p>Getting started with the ESP32 microcontroller</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="content-body">
                <div class="loading" id="loading-indicator">
                    <div class="loading-spinner"></div>
                    <p>Loading content...</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="content-section" id="content-container">
                    <div class="section">
                        <p>The ESP32 is a powerful, low-cost microcontroller with integrated Wi-Fi and Bluetooth capabilities. This guide will help you learn how to interface with various electronic components using the ESP32.</p>
                        
                        <img src="https://randomnerdtutorials.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ESP32-DOIT-DEVKIT-V1-Board-Pinout-36-GPIOs-updated.jpg" alt="ESP32 Development Board" class="component-image">
                        <p class="image-caption">ESP32 Development Board</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="section">
                        <h3 class="section-title">Getting Started</h3>
                        <p>Before working with components, make sure you have:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>An ESP32 development board</li>
                            <li>USB cable for programming</li>
                            <li>Arduino IDE or PlatformIO installed</li>
                            <li>Basic electronic components (breadboard, jumper wires, resistors)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="note">
                        <div class="note-title">Learning Path</div>
                        <p>We recommend following these steps for beginners:</p>
                        <ol>
                            <li>Start with <a href="basic-electronics.html">Basic Electronics</a></li>
                            <li>Understand <a href="input-output-pins.html">Input/Output Pins</a></li>
                            <li>Try simple <a href="leds.html">LED projects</a></li>
                            <li>Move to <a href="buttons.html">button inputs</a></li>
                            <li>Explore more advanced components</li>
                        </ol>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="section">
                        <h3 class="section-title">Key Features</h3>
                        <p>The ESP32 offers several advantages:</p>
                        
                        <table class="pin-table">
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Feature</th>
                                    <th>Description</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Dual-Core Processor</td>
                                    <td>Two Xtensa 32-bit LX6 CPUs at 240MHz</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Wireless Connectivity</td>
                                    <td>Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n and Bluetooth 4.2</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>GPIO Pins</td>
                                    <td>Up to 36 programmable pins</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Analog Inputs</td>
                                    <td>18 channels of 12-bit ADC</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Low Power</td>
                                    <td>Multiple sleep modes for battery operation</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
